<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
In process_long_param the code uses memcmp(param, "version", MHD_STATICSTR_LEN_("version")) to compare param (declared as const char * and representing a null-terminated parameter string) against a string literal. MISRA C 2023 Rule 21.14 forbids using memcmp to compare null-terminated strings. This use therefore violates the rule (use strcmp/strncmp or a dedicated string comparison function instead).
</scenario>
